comments.body:
[~mmunn1]: The only concern is that this fix doesn't address the fact that an exception/error response from the WalrusImageManager is not causing an error response to the client. It should be returning a 50* error. I suspect it is a problem with the specific exception type not being caught in the Walrus outbound bindings.

Recommendations:
1. Catch a broader type of exceptions, either Exception, or PersistenceException in the catch block where you currently catch the RollbackException.
2. Add a broad try-catch around the entire method that passes on WalrusExceptions but wraps all others in a new WalrusException would be safest as well to ensure that any exception that does escape does not result in an HTTP 200 response, but an error that the NC will handle and not save the response content.

{code}
try {
    <body of getDecryptedImage method>
} catch(WalrusException e ) {
   throw e;
} catch(Exception e) {
   throw new WalrusException("InternalError", "Internal error getting image: " + e.getMessage(), 
                    "decryptedImage", 
                    bucketName + "/" + objectKey, 
                    HttpResponseStatus.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR);
}
{code}
